<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sea Savvy</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=League+Spartan:wght@400;700&family=Glacial+Indifference:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
<nav class="navbar">
    <ul class="nav-left">
        <li class="menu-icon">
            <a href="#" id="menu-toggle">&#9776;</a> <!-- Menu icon (hamburger) -->
        </li>
        <li class="logo">
            <a href="/" class="nav-brand">Sea Savvy</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <ul class="nav-right">
        <li class="username-dropdown">
            <i class="fas fa-user user-icon"></i> <!-- User icon -->
            <a href="#" id="username-toggle"><%= username %></a> <!-- Dynamic username -->
            <div id="user-dropdown" class="dropdown-content">
                <a href="/profile"><i class="fas fa-user"></i> Profile</a> <!-- Profile icon -->
                <a href="/rewards"><i class="fas fa-gem"></i> Points and Rewards</a> <!-- Gem icon -->
                <a href="/settings"><i class="fas fa-cog"></i> Settings</a> <!-- Settings icon -->
                <a href="/help"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Help Center</a> <!-- Help icon -->
                <a href="/logout"><i class="fas fa-sign-out-alt"></i> Logout</a> <!-- Logout icon -->
            </div>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <div id="dropdown-menu" class="dropdown-content">
        <a href="/seaquest"><i class="fas fa-gamepad"></i> Sea Quest</a>
        <a href="/seascholar"><i class="fas fa-book"></i> Sea Scholar</a>
        <a href="/marinemonitor"><i class="fas fa-bullhorn"></i> Marine Monitor</a>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h2>Hey <%= username %>! <br>Start leveling up and building your weekly streak!</h2> <!-- Dynamic username -->
        <span class="week-streak">
            <i class="fas fa-fire fire-icon"></i> <!-- Fire icon -->
            <span class="week-number"><%= streak %></span> <!-- Dynamic streak -->
            <h2> Week Streak</h2>
        </span>
        <span class="level"><h2>LEVEL <%= level %></h2></span> <!-- Dynamic level -->
    </div>
    <hr class="custom-line">
    <div class="info-section">
        <div class="info-left">
            <h2><%= username %></h2> <!-- Dynamic username -->
            <p>Role: <%= role %></p> <!-- Dynamic role -->
            <p>Email: <%= email %></p> <!-- Dynamic email -->
        </div>
        <div class="info-right">
            <h3>POINTS <%= points %></h3> <!-- Dynamic points -->
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="custom-line">
    <div class="image-text-section">
        <img src="game2.png" alt="game picture" class="image">
        <div class="text">
            <h3>Sea Quest</h3>
            <p>Discover the ocean’s secrets with our engaging game <b>Sea Quest</b> that brings real data to life!<br>It's as educational as it is entertaining.
                This decision-driven experience helps students construct explanations, reason effectively, and become self-directed learners involving marine science and ocean literacy.<br>
                <br>The game can be played in the browser with the button below.  
            </p>
            <div class="button-section">
                <a href="/seaquest" class="launch-btn">Launch Sea Quest</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="image-text-section-reverse">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h3>Sea Scholar</h3>
            <p>Easily access a wide variety of resources - articles, courses and much more using <b>Sea Scholar</b>!<br>It's time to make learning fun and easy using our personalised Educational Hub.
                Students, researchers, scholars, and enthusiasts have easy access to organised information, maps, courses, and more, increasing accessibility to Ocean Literacy.<br>
                <br>Access the Educational Hub by clicking the button below.  
            </p>
            <div class="button-section">
                <a href="/seascholar" class="launch-btn">Open Sea Scholar</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-content">
            <img src="edu3.png" alt="Education img">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="image-text-section">
        <img src="news.png" alt="news pic" class="image">
        <div class="text">
            <h3>Marine Monitor</h3>
            <p>Introducing <b>Marine Monitor</b>, your go-to source for real-time updates on ocean conditions and safety alerts.<br>
                Stay informed with the latest news, weather forecasts, and alerts about storms, tsunamis, and other marine events.
                 With Marine Monitor, you can navigate the ocean confidently, ensuring you’re always prepared for whatever lies ahead.
                <br><br>Go to Marine Monitor by clicking the button below.
            </p>
            <div class="button-section">
                <a href="/marinemonitor" class="launch-btn">Go to Marine Monitor</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
